The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for action recognition in videos, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The study also explores the performance of different architectures and datasets, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects. The paper uses pretraining and transfer learning techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the study involves training very deep CNNs, which is a topic of interest in neural networks (cs.NE) research.
